From 510a30dedb670f0cf7b2894e9935d7eff9293ad4 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Alankar Changes <changes@alankarfashions.com>
Date: Sun, 12 Jul 2026 14:13:16 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix(layout): harden getBrand/generateMetadata against
 server-render crash
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- getSupabaseAdmin() now returns null instead of throwing when env vars missing
- getBrand() defensively coerces jsonb column values to plain objects (handles null/string/array edge cases)
- generateMetadata() wrapped in try/catch with sensible fallback metadata
- Validate metadataBase URL with fallback to production URL
- Root cause: on fresh page loads, generateMetadata + RootLayout both run server-side
  and any malformed settings.value jsonb (e.g. null, array, or string in brand/seo/analytics
  keys) caused prop access downstream in <Analytics/> Script rendering to throw during
  hydration. Now every layer returns safe defaults.

fix(header): mobile menu now correctly slides in from LEFT with dark backdrop

- Moved drawer + backdrop out of <header sticky> stacking context (was nested inside
  the sticky positioned parent, causing z-index/fixed positioning quirks on iOS)
- Drawer is now a sibling to header inside SiteHeader fragment
- Backdrop z-[60], drawer z-[70] for reliable stacking
- Body scroll lock preserved via existing useEffect
- Added aria-hidden and data-testids for accessibility & testing

feat(admin): remove Admin button from public storefront header (desktop + mobile)

- Removes admin link from customer-facing site header (both desktop nav and mobile drawer)
- Admins can still access /admin directly by URL — panel itself is untouched

feat(payment): Cash on Delivery (COD) end-to-end

- Checkout page: payment method selector (Online vs COD), COD eligibility rules,
  handling fee display, min/max order thresholds
- API /api/checkout/create: skips Razorpay when payment_method=cod; creates order with
  status=processing, payment_status=cod_pending; sends dedicated COD confirmation email
- New email template (lib/email.js: sendCODOrderConfirmation) with 'Pay on Delivery'
  language, cash amount emphasized, no 'payment received' wording
- Public /api/cod-config endpoint reads settings.cod for the checkout page
- Admin settings: new COD section with enable toggle, handling fee, min/max order limits
- Admin orders: COD badge on listing, 'Mark Payment Collected' button on detail modal;
  new /api/admin/orders/:id/cod-collected endpoint (marks paid + decrements stock now)
- Order detail page: shows 'Pay on Delivery' banner, correct payment status labels,
  landmark & alternate phone in shipping address

feat(checkout): expanded fields for Indian addresses

- Added alternate phone, landmark, delivery notes/instructions, billing-same-as-shipping
- Address schema in lib/validators.js accepts alt_phone and landmark

feat(auth): Continue with Google (Supabase OAuth)

- Google button on both login and signup pages (with Google logo SVG)
- OAuth redirect to /auth/callback which exchanges the code, then upserts a
  profiles row for new Google users so admin customer list & downstream flows work
- Uses next param for post-login redirect target

feat(admin/products): jewellery-specific fields

- Material / metal type, weight (grams), care instructions
- Low-stock threshold per product, set_group (link related items)
- Bestseller flag (separate from featured/new/trending)
- Validators updated to accept new fields

feat(admin/categories): full CRUD with SEO & branding

- Rewrote page with banner image, short description, is_featured toggle, edit support
- API PATCH via upsert on categories POST endpoint (existing id triggers update)

migrations: additive-only feature migration

- supabase/migration_features.sql — ONLY adds new columns (payment_method, cod_fee,
  notes on orders; material/weight_grams/care_instructions/low_stock_threshold/
  set_group/is_bestseller on products; banner_url/description/is_featured on categories)
- Seeds sensible COD default (enabled, ₹0 fee, ₹0 min, ₹15,000 max)
- Never drops, never alters existing data
- Exposed at /api/setup/migration-features for easy copy-paste to Supabase SQL editor
